{% set pageTitle = 'NHS.UK frontend library' %}
{% set pageDescription = 'The code you need to start building user interfaces for NHS websites and services' %}

{% extends 'includes/layout.njk' %}
{% from 'components/review-date/macro.njk' import reviewDate %}

{% block body %}
<div class="nhsuk-grid-row">
  <div class="nhsuk-grid-column-two-thirds">
    <h1 class="nhsuk-u-margin-bottom-5">{{pageTitle}}</h1>
    <p class="nhsuk-body-l">{{pageDescription}}</p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="nhsuk-grid-row nhsuk-u-margin-top-8">
  <div class="nhsuk-grid-column-one-third">
    <h2 class="nhsuk-heading-s nhsuk-u-margin-bottom-3">
      <a href="https://github.com/nhsuk/nhsuk-frontend">Frontend library on GitHub</a>
    </h2>
    <p>Use the code and contribute to it.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="nhsuk-grid-row">
  <div class="nhsuk-grid-column-two-thirds nhsuk-u-margin-top-8">
    <h2>Use the code</h2>
    <p>Use the frontend library to:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>get the latest, tested code</li>
      <li>build something that fits with the rest of the NHS website</li>
      <li>save the NHS money</li>
      <li>join the community of people improving and adding to it</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>What is a frontend library?</h2>
    <p>We've made our production code available to NHS developers and designers in a "frontend library". The code in the library will help you build accessible websites with an NHS look and feel. You'll also get tested components and patterns.</p>
    <p>Our <a href="https://github.com/nhsuk/nhsuk-frontend">frontend library</a> is in GitHub. You need to sign up to GitHub to use it.</p>

    <h2>Get in touch</h2>
    <p>You can <a href="https://github.com/nhsuk/nhsuk-frontend/tree/master/docs/contributing">contribute</a> code via GitHub.</p>
    <p>And you can contact us on the <a href="https://nhsuk.slack.com/messages/standards">NHSUK #standards Slack channel</a> or email the standards team at service-manual@nhs.net.</p>

    {{ reviewDate({
      "lastReview": "January 2019"
    }) }}
  </div>
  </div>
</div>
{% endblock %}
